  m_QuestionText:
  - FontSize: 2
    Text: In UI Toolkit, how can you specify that a style should only apply when
      an element is hovered over by the mouse?
  m_QuestionImage: {fileID: 0}
  m_Skills: UI Toolkit
  m_ShuffleAnswers: 0
  m_Answers:
  - IsCorrect: 1
    Text: Using <b>:hover</b> pseudo-class
  - IsCorrect: 0
    Text: Using <b>hover</b> attribute
  - IsCorrect: 0
    Text: Using <b>onMouseHover</b> event
  - IsCorrect: 0
    Text: Using <b>HoverHandler</b> class
  m_FeedbackCorrect: In Unity's UI Toolkit, the <b>:hover</b> pseudo-class is used
    to apply styles when an element is hovered over by the mouse. This allows you
    to create interactive and responsive designs in your user interface.
  m_FeedbackIncorrect: In Unity's UI Toolkit, styles for an element during a hover
    event are specified using the <b>:hover</b> pseudo-class. Using a hover attribute,
    onMouseHover event, or a hypothetical HoverHandler class are not valid methods
    in UI Toolkit to specify styles for a hover event.
